## Visual

A dark, starry, gold-trimmed poster compares ordinary graph adjacency on the left with directed chiral adjacency on the right, divided by a vertical gold line. The left diagram shows an undirected graph and muted blue spectrum, while the right shows a directed cycle with phase labels and a bright rainbow interference spectrum. Ornamental borders, celestial imagery, serif typography, and symbols like \(e^{i\phi}\) frame chirality as both a mathematical and metaphysical orientation principle.
